    This version adds a dry friction term proportional to the sign of velocity,
    which is common in mechanical oscillators with Coulomb friction.
    
    Physical reasoning:
    - Restoring force: linear and cubic in position (odd powers)
    - Damping force: linear, cubic, quadratic in velocity plus sign(velocity) for dry friction
    - Cross terms between position and velocity to capture coupling effects
    - Non-smooth effects via absolute values of position and velocity
    
    Parameters:
    - x0: position at time t (np.ndarray)
    - x1: velocity at time t (np.ndarray)
